  "name": "Sediment Drift (Obrix)",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "Peaceful resolve — fine particles suspended in a slow current, settling over time. Drift Bus is the engine soul: driftRate=0.011, driftDepth=0.92, the highest driftDepth in this collection. Journey Mode allows the sediment to keep settling without interruption. Saw src1 at -12 semitones (sub register) with Noise src2 very low in mix (0.15) for the grain. proc1=LP (480 Hz, gentle reso 0.2) shapes the cloud. LFO->Pan (slow, 0.009 Hz) gently rotates the stereo field like a deep current; Env->FilterCutoff (slow bloom); Velocity->Volume; Aftertouch->FXMix. The peaceful end of the Submerged collection — not deep darkness but serene acceptance.",
